Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.99,0:01:43.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,With the death of Sibylla Mamiina,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.67,0:01:47.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,and the ancient Simoun having fallen\N into the hands of the Islanders,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.42,0:01:49.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,they’re now on an\N equal footing with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.72,0:01:52.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,Rather, because of their\N expertise in warfare,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.48,0:01:53.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,they are now a serious threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.75,0:01:55.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,I still believe…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.34,0:01:59.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,…it may have been reckless to send Chor Tempest out like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.01,0:02:03.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,But didn’t Chor Tempest deliver a crippling blow to their airborne base?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.46,0:02:07.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,They’ll need time \Nto reorganize their forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.48,0:02:10.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,The enemy will be unable \Nto attack us any time soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.07,0:02:13.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,The sibylla’s death has at least bought us some time. Is that not so?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.35,0:02:20.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let me remind you that Tempus Spatium\N is watching everything you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.03,0:02:30.00,Titles,,85,0,0,,{\blur0.6}Elegy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.36,0:03:00.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Dominura… Limone… \NI bet they’re dead too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.88,0:03:01.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,Floe…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.61,0:03:06.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,All of them…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.04,0:03:07.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,They all died!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.89,0:03:09.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s gonna be our turn next!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.76,0:03:11.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,Every last one of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.37,0:03:13.29,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’re gonna die, I just know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.76,0:03:22.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,— You’re appalling.\N— What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.26,0:03:27.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,War is nothing but mass murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.45,0:03:30.77,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you can’t live with that, then I suggest you go to the Spring immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.15,0:03:44.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,I wonder why… it had to be Mamiina?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.17,0:03:57.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,I wonder why… it had to be Mamiina?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:02.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,I can’t even cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.36,0:04:05.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,When Amuria died…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.16,0:04:09.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, at that moment,\N my heart died with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.28,0:04:17.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’ve been hurting everyone’s feelings, \Nand pushing everyone away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.65,0:04:23.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,But despite everything, \NI can’t shed even a single tear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.51,0:04:25.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,I just live on with my \Nheart dead inside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.74,0:04:29.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:31.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,If I had died in Mamiina’s place…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.87,0:04:48.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Emerald…?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.86,0:04:59.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,Have you been here all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.40,0:05:01.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,Are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.57,0:05:09.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,If I… had been stronger,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.50,0:05:13.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamiina wouldn’t have died.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.40,0:05:17.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,If I’d…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.49,0:05:21.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,No. If anyone is to blame, \Nit’s me. I was her pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.54,0:05:23.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,It had nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.96,0:05:26.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don’t say it has nothing to do with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.69,0:05:44.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aaeru…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.40,0:05:46.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.29,0:05:51.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,Didn’t you tell me that\N you weren’t afraid of anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:05:55.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,Amuria!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.27,0:05:57.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s why we need to get stronger!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.92,0:05:59.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,You understand, don’t you, Neviril?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:04.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,We can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.67,0:06:08.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,I have to live.
Comment: 0,0:06:08.84,0:06:10.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.76,0:06:15.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,I… have to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.98,0:06:20.22,Regular,,0,0,0,,I have to!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.40,0:06:28.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,But the one who lies behind me is the Simulacrum Theocracy’s most revered sibylla,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.99,0:06:31.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aurea Neviril!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:33.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,She’s going to get out of here safely,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.87,0:06:37.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,and I won’t let you lay a finger on her!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.79,0:06:39.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.78,0:06:42.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,We must live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.60,0:07:15.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,Shall I get you a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.87,0:07:27.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,“Again?”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.07,0:07:31.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,You make it sound like\Nwe used to be friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.43,0:07:36.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,The truth {of the matter }is that one of us was always meant to be on top, and the other below.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.07,0:07:37.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.31,0:07:41.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sheesh, what were you\N thinking back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.56,0:07:43.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,I wanted to be friends…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.33,0:07:44.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.69,0:07:50.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,I truly want to be friends with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.27,0:07:55.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamiina!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.57,0:07:58.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,So please stop saying “but we {\i1}are{\i0} friends!” and stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.46,0:08:00.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m a little sensitive about it, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.95,0:08:03.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.12,0:08:22.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,I have called for\N Onashia from the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.07,0:08:23.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,And the Defence Ministry?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.93,0:08:27.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,As you have ordered,\N they are unaware of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.59,0:08:31.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,They look forward to fighting \Nwith such eager eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.63,0:08:33.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,How terribly sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.07,0:08:38.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,This world has been\N defiled by hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.80,0:08:41.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yet they cling to this sterile land…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.50,0:08:45.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,…and persist in their foolish desire to fight until they annihilate each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.88,0:08:50.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,Now, we must not \Nwaste any more time!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.61,0:08:53.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,We must crawl out from \Nthis accursed place!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.82,0:08:57.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,We must follow the path of Tempus Spatium,\N and open the door to the New World!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.89,0:08:59.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,The New World?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.65,0:09:04.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes, and to achieve this, Anubituf,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.39,0:09:07.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,I may have to ask a great deal of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.31,0:09:10.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,To begin with, the legendary choir,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:12.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,Chor Dextra, must be revived.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.70,0:09:22.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,Our Simoun outperform it \Nby a small margin in several areas,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.66,0:09:25.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,but it doesn’t look like there are any really significant differences.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.75,0:09:29.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Morinas?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.97,0:09:38.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,Is Neviril’s Simoun…?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.72,0:09:39.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.86,0:09:42.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Taking apart the ancient\N Simoun comes first?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.26,0:09:45.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,Everything else will\N have to wait, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.12,0:09:47.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,Not that I’m blaming you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.60,0:09:50.77,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s not like you can \Ndisobey your orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.77,0:09:52.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,Actually…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.38,0:09:54.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,I wanted to do this first, too.
Comment: 0,0:09:54.40,0:09:55.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.46,0:09:58.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Morinas…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.37,0:10:03.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,Won’t you please go to the Spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.41,0:10:13.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,I can’t right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.06,0:10:15.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Simoun are cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.85,0:10:18.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don’t really care\N about the Simoun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.26,0:10:19.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.38,0:10:22.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,“As long as I can fly a Simoun,\N I don’t care about anything else!”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.55,0:10:25.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,“I don’t have to care about my choirmates!” That’s what I thought until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.78,0:10:27.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,Things aren’t like that any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.49,0:10:31.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’ve changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.27,0:10:34.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,You too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.86,0:10:53.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,Now that we’ve lost Mamiina,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.09,0:10:55.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,I wonder if they’re gonna \Nrearrange our pairs again?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.92,0:10:58.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.42,0:11:02.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,Unless we get another person, someone will have to be left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.10,0:11:06.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Para-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.92,0:11:11.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, Para-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.76,0:11:14.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don’t ask me.
Comment: 0,0:11:14.48,0:11:15.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.98,0:11:18.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,I… don’t have the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.97,0:11:22.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,Para-sama…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.45,0:11:29.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,How can I apologize \Nto Mamiina, who died?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.77,0:11:32.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,I was so preoccupied with myself…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.88,0:11:37.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,…that I didn’t perform properly as a member of Chor Tempest!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.05,0:11:40.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m so useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.51,0:11:41.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,When did it happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.68,0:11:42.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.72,0:11:45.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,How did I sink so low?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.75,0:11:46.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.55,0:11:49.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,Para-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.52,0:11:54.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,Alti?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.98,0:11:58.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t matter if it’s a lie.
Comment: 0,0:11:58.66,0:11:59.22,Regular,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.44,0:12:02.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,As long as you’re always\N “Para-sama,” I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.70,0:12:08.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t matter if you’re wrong, so long as you make firm decisions!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.92,0:12:11.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,I know you’re suffering too, Paraietta!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.88,0:12:16.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,But… as long as you’re \N“our gallant Para-sama,”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.97,0:12:19.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,you give everyone hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.21,0:12:22.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,When you say “everyone,”\N you mean Kaimu, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.25,0:12:27.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why do you go so far for her?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.46,0:12:29.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,I wanted to see {Nee-san}her smile again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.99,0:12:33.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s why I wanted to become a man. That’s why I wanted to become stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.89,0:12:36.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s all because I wanted\N to make {Nee-san}her happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.98,0:12:38.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,But I realized something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.84,0:12:42.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,She won’t be {able to smile again}happy as long as\N I keep getting in her way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.37,0:12:55.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,That being the case, \Nthere’s only one thing I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.76,0:13:07.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,For my sister’s sake,\N I will distance myself from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.10,0:13:18.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,Paraietta-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.56,0:13:19.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Paraietta-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.98,0:13:21.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Floe is—!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.32,0:13:22.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,Floe?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.65,0:13:24.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.17,0:13:39.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,Floe!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.09,0:13:41.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,Floe! What are you doing\N with that suitcase?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.71,0:13:43.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.05,0:13:45.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,— What do you mean, leaving?\N— I’m going to the Spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.09,0:13:49.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don’t bother trying to stop me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.43,0:13:52.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,I want nothing to do\Nwith this “war” thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.10,0:13:53.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,And I have no intention to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.56,0:13:56.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait! Let’s talk this \Nover with everyone first.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.45,0:14:03.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,Rodoreamon…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.08,0:14:14.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that…?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.79,0:14:24.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.05,0:14:26.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that… a reconnaissance Simile?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.85,0:14:29.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Where are they going\N at this time of night?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.15,0:14:36.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamiina!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.59,0:14:45.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Mamiina’s remains are being sent\N to the lands where she was raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.45,0:14:53.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why? Why did you…?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.61,0:14:56.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Those are Her Eminence’s wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.00,0:14:58.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,To console Sibylla Mamiina’s spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.66,0:15:02.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,it was her belief that she should be returned\N to the land which was dear to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:07.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,But that could have been done after her funeral\N was performed here, on the {\i1}Arcus Prima{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.61,0:15:10.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re absolutely right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.26,0:15:13.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,She died honourably, \Nas befits a Simoun sibylla.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.63,0:15:16.22,Regular,,0,0,0,,It should have been our duty\N to give her a proper burial.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.22,0:15:18.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Died… honourably?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:20.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,Enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.57,0:15:26.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,Vyura?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.40,0:15:28.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Vyura.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.61,0:15:33.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,In place of Mamiina, she will now be piloting a Simoun with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.37,0:15:34.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.70,0:15:39.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,We will have to reorganize \Nthe pairs immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.10,0:15:42.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,We will choose the pairs which can create the strongest Ri Maajons…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.47,0:15:44.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,Minister!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:47.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,We have just lost\N our beloved comrade!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.01,0:15:51.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,To perform any Ri Maajon, \Nour spirits must be clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.83,0:15:54.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,It is an act performed\N with the purity of the mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.30,0:15:55.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’re still—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.26,0:15:56.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,What a carefree thing to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.68,0:15:58.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.18,0:16:02.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,Do you want Sibylla Mamiina’s\N sacrifice to go to waste?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.24,0:16:16.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.46,0:16:28.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.42,0:16:31.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,I can’t believe they won’t \Neven let us say goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.08,0:16:33.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Defence Minister’s \Njust like that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.43,0:16:35.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,The war is all he thinks about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.12,0:16:37.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,They don’t care about\N Mamiina’s death at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.85,0:16:47.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamiina… She didn’t come \Nfrom a sibylla family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.49,0:16:53.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamiina was right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.75,0:16:56.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,I really am just “Her Little Ladyship!”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.74,0:16:58.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamiina’s feelings…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.60,0:17:00.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,I wanted to understand them!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.62,0:17:01.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.75,0:17:03.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,I didn’t understand at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.98,0:17:06.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,You wish to understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.33,0:17:08.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.62,0:17:12.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamiina’s feelings are right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.91,0:17:29.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Mamiina’s soul is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.50,0:17:36.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Her soul accepts the end of her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.49,0:17:37.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.42,0:17:41.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,To her, her death had meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.41,0:17:42.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,You…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.75,0:17:46.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,You must not touch Onashia-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.65,0:17:48.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,Bring it forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.73,0:17:49.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes, milady.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.17,0:17:57.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,Accepts the end of her life?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.13,0:17:59.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,I hate things like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.05,0:18:00.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,Floe…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.47,0:18:02.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,Is it supposed to\N make us feel better?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.57,0:18:05.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,How can anyone know \Nhow the dead feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.73,0:18:07.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,Rodoreamon?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.23,0:18:18.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,You know…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.52,0:18:21.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,I always envied \Nthose braids of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.04,0:18:23.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,But this…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.60,0:18:27.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,…was the way your parents \Ntold you to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.52,0:18:32.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t something that\N a child would have understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.04,0:18:35.22,Regular,,0,0,0,,It was just Her Little Ladyship’s hairstyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.24,0:18:37.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Back then, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.17,0:18:43.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to truly be friends with Mamiina. That’s why I…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.39,0:18:46.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,Wh-What in the world are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.78,0:18:51.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s why I…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.31,0:18:55.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,She honestly wanted to be\N friends with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.07,0:19:04.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamiina!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.31,0:19:06.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamiina!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.41,0:19:24.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamiina is a Simoun sibylla!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.56,0:19:26.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.10,0:19:33.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,And Simoun sibyllae \Naren’t just here to fight!{I'm inclined to agree with the R1 subtitles - Simoun sibyllae didn't come here to fight at all.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.61,0:19:37.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.07,0:19:38.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.82,0:19:40.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.82,0:19:42.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,Rodoreamon!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.86,0:19:44.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let’s go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.33,0:19:52.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,If everyone’s going, \Nwon’t you need another pair?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.83,0:19:54.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,Vyura!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.38,0:19:57.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,Everyone else from \NChor Rubor went to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.21,0:19:59.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why do you think I stayed behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.47,0:20:02.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,For the same reason as Mamiina!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.30,0:20:04.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s because I wanted \Nto stay a Simoun sibylla.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.96,0:20:10.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,Vyura, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.74,0:20:27.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.49,0:20:29.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.46,0:20:37.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,How dare they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.35,0:20:39.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Who is responsible for \Nthis insubordination?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.51,0:20:49.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,What are they doing, in the middle of a state of emergency?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.38,0:20:55.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’ll start off with Mamiina’s specialty,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.79,0:20:57.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,the Ri Maajon of the Raging Sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.44,0:20:59.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.74,0:21:10.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,Next, let’s do the Dandelion Ri Maajon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.74,0:21:24.22,Regular,,0,0,0,,So this is who we are…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.22,0:21:25.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.93,0:21:30.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yeah! We’re…!{lol, telepathy...}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.21,0:21:33.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aa… eru.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.49,0:21:51.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibyllae!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.33,0:21:54.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,We draw our prayers\N upon the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.38,0:22:01.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibyllae.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.71,0:22:08.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,For the tomorrows \Nthat will never cease,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.39,0:22:13.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,and for the yesterdays which have already been spun, we offer our prayers!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.77,0:22:20.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibyllae…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.77,0:22:23.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.65,0:22:26.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,We are!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.00,0:24:06.67,Titles,,85,0,0,,{\blur0.6}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.67,0:24:11.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,Tempus Spatium grants\N us another possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.59,0:24:15.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,Next time, on Simoun:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.55,0:24:17.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Door to a New World.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.55,0:24:20.02,Titles,,85,0,0,,{\blur0.6}The Door to a New World
